  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“I shouldn’t think you’d want that shawl!” Daisy exclaimed."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“Well I do!” her mother answered with a little laugh."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“Did you get Randolph to go to bed?” asked the young girl."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“No; I couldn’t induce him,” said Mrs. Miller very gently. “He wants to talk to the waiter. He likes to talk to that waiter.”"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“I was telling Mr. Winterbourne,” the young girl went on; and to the young man’s ear her tone might have indicated that she had been uttering his name all her life."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“Oh, yes!” said Winterbourne; “I have the pleasure of knowing your son.”"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "Randolph’s mamma was silent; she turned her attention to the lake. But at last she spoke. “Well, I don’t see how he lives!”"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“Anyhow, it isn’t so bad as it was at Dover,” said Daisy Miller."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "“And what occurred at Dover?” Winterbourne asked."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
